 Two people were shot in Shallcross in Durban on Tuesday
morning. Rescue Care spokesman, Garrith Jamieson said on arrival
Paramedics, found two men believed to be in their forties had been shot inside
a mechanical workshop. “One man had sustained a gunshot wound to his head and there
was nothing more Paramedics could do for him and he was declared deceased on
the scene,” said Jamieson. “The second man had sustained a gunshot wound and other
injuries and was in a critical condition. Advanced Life Support Paramedics
worked to stabilise the man on scene by placing him on a ventilator before
rushing him through to a nearby Hospital for the further care that he
required,” he added. At this stage the events leading up to the shooting is
unknown however SAPS were on the scene and will be investigating further. 